headline.main: Earl Warren, 83, Who Led High Court In Time of Vast Social Change, Is Dead; His 16 Years as Justice Had Profound Impact on Law and Life Former Chief Justice Warren Dead in Capital at 83 A Liberal Record 16 Years on Bench

snippet: Earl Warren, who as Chief Justice of the United States presided over extraordinary constitutional change, died tonight at Georgetown University Hospital. He was 83 years old. Earl Warren

byline.original: By ANTHONY LEWISSpecial to The New York Times
